com.nabto.api

Class NabtoClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.nabto.api.NabtoClient

  • public class NabtoClient
extends java.lang.Object
    The NabtoClient is a simple way to communicate with a Nabto device.

    Currently, streams and tunnels are not supported. Use NabtoApi to access all Nabto client API features.

    Example:

    
 NabtoClient client = new NabtoClient(this);
 client.init("guest", "");
 UrlResult result = client.fetchUrl("nabto://demo1.nabduino.net/temperature.json?");
 if (result.getStatus() == NabtoStatus.OK) {
     String html = new String(result.getResult());
     // do something with HTML string
 }

                        java.lang.String password)
        Initialize the Nabto application using a specified profile.
        Parameters:
        email - The id of an existing certificate.
        password - Password for encrypted private key file.
        Returns:
        If the function succeeds, the return value is NabtoStatus.OK. If the function fails, the return value is one of the following values.

        • NabtoStatus.PORTAL_LOGIN_FAILURE

        • NabtoStatus.OPEN_CERT_OR_PK_FAILED (unprobable)
        • NabtoStatus.API_NOT_INITIALIZED (unprobable)
        • NabtoStatus.ERROR_READING_CONFIG (unprobable)
        • NabtoStatus.FAILED (unprobable)

      • probeNetwork

        public NabtoStatus probeNetwork()
        Try to connect to probe service to test for network connectivity.

        If NULL is specified as host, the portal host name from the configuration is used.

        This function can be used to make the underlying platform start the network.

        Returns:
        If the function succeeds, the return value is NabtoStatus.OK. If the function fails, the return value is one of the following values.
        • NabtoStatus.NO_NETWORK: The host couldn't be reached.
        • NabtoStatus.ERROR_READING_CONFIG: The config file wasn't read.
        • NabtoStatus.FAILED: The path to home directory wasn't found OR error in the C API wrapper

      • signup

        public NabtoStatus signup(java.lang.String email,
                          java.lang.String password)
        Signs up for a Nabto account on the portal (host name defined in the configuration file). Invokes web service and initiates sending of confirmation email.
        Parameters:
        email - Email address of user to register on portal.
        password - Requested password for portal.
        Returns:
        If the function succeeds, the return value is NabtoStatus.OK. If the function fails, the return value is one of the following values.
        • NabtoStatus.NO_NETWORK: The host couldn't be reached.
        • NabtoStatus.ERROR_READING_CONFIG: The config file wasn't read.
        • NabtoStatus.INVALID_ADDRESS: Invalid email address.
        • NabtoStatus.ADDRESS_IN_USE: Email address already in use.
        • NabtoStatus.FAILED: Unknown error.

      • rpcSetDefaultInterface

        public RpcResult rpcSetDefaultInterface(java.lang.String interfaceDefinition)
        Sets the default RPC interface to use when later invoking rpcInvoke(String).

        Can be overriden for specific hosts with rpcSetInterface(String, String).

        If a non-API level error occurred (RpcResult.getStatus() returns NabtoStatus.FAILED_WITH_JSON_MESSAGE), RpcResult.getJson() contains error details. Otherwise, the JSON string is undefined.

        Parameters:
        interfaceDefinition - The interface definition as XML formatted string.
        Returns:
        A RpcResult object. If the function succeeds, the return value of RpcResult.getStatus() is NabtoStatus.OK. If the function fails, the return value of RpcResult.getStatus() is one of the following values.
        • NabtoStatus.ERROR_READING_CONFIG: The config file wasn't read.
        • NabtoStatus.INVALID_SESSION: Session handle was invalid. See init(String, String)
        • NabtoStatus.FAILED_WITH_JSON_MESSAGE: An error occurred with details in RpcResult.getJson().
        • NabtoStatus.FAILED: Unknown error.

      • rpcSetInterface

        public RpcResult rpcSetInterface(java.lang.String nabtoHost,
                                 java.lang.String interfaceDefinition)
        Sets the RPC interface to use for a specific host when later invoking rpcInvoke(String).

        If a non-API level error occurred (RpcResult.getStatus() returns NabtoStatus.FAILED_WITH_JSON_MESSAGE), RpcResult.getJson() contains error details. Otherwise, the JSON string is undefined.

        Parameters:
        nabtoHost - The host for which the interface is to be used later RPC invocations.
        interfaceDefinition - The interface definition as XML formatted string.
        Returns:
        A RpcResult object. If the function succeeds, the return value of RpcResult.getStatus() is NabtoStatus.OK. If the function fails, the return value of RpcResult.getStatus() is one of the following values.
        • NabtoStatus.ERROR_READING_CONFIG: The config file wasn't read.
        • NabtoStatus.INVALID_SESSION: Session handle was invalid. See init(String, String)
        • NabtoStatus.FAILED_WITH_JSON_MESSAGE: An error occurred with details in RpcResult.getJson().
        • NabtoStatus.FAILED: Unknown error.

      • rpcInvoke

        public RpcResult rpcInvoke(java.lang.String nabtoUrl)
        Retrieves data synchronously from specified nabto://URL.

        As compared to fetchUrl(String), this function only supports function invocation and not displaying contents of an HTML DD bundle. This also means the interface file is to specified prior to invocation using either rpcSetInterface(String, String) or rpcSetDefaultInterface(String)

        If a non-API level error occurred (RpcResult.getStatus() returns NabtoStatus.FAILED_WITH_JSON_MESSAGE), RpcResult.getJson() contains error details. Otherwise, the JSON string is undefined.

        On successful return (RpcResult.getStatus() returns NabtoStatus.OK), RpcResult.getJson() returns a JSON response representing the response document. Otherwise, the JSON response contains details about the occured error.

        Parameters:
        nabtoUrl - The URL to retrieve.
        Returns:
        A RpcResult object. If the function succeeds, the return value of RpcResult.getStatus() is NabtoStatus.OK and RpcResult.getJson() returns the JSON response. If the function fails, the return value of RpcResult.getStatus() is one of the following values.
        • NabtoStatus.ERROR_READING_CONFIG: The config file wasn't read.
        • NabtoStatus.INVALID_SESSION: Session handle was invalid. See init(String, String)
        • NabtoStatus.FAILED_WITH_JSON_MESSAGE: An error occurred, details can be found in JSON format in the response
        • NabtoStatus.FAILED: Unknown error.

      • fetchUrl

        public UrlResult fetchUrl(java.lang.String nabtoUrl)
        Retrieves data synchronously from specified nabto://URL.

        On successful return (UrlResult.getStatus() returns NabtoStatus.OK), UrlResult.getResult() returns the HTML code. The MIME type of the data is returned by UrlResult.getMimeType().

        Parameters:
        nabtoUrl - The URL to retrieve.
        Returns:
        A UrlResult object. If the function succeeds, the return value of UrlResult.getStatus() is NabtoStatus.OK and UrlResult.getResult() returns the HTML code. If the function fails, the return value of UrlResult.getStatus() is one of the following values.
        • NabtoStatus.ERROR_READING_CONFIG: The config file wasn't read.
        • NabtoStatus.INVALID_SESSION: Session handle was invalid. See init(String, String)
        • NabtoStatus.FAILED: Unknown error.

      • submitPostData

        public UrlResult submitPostData(java.lang.String nabtoUrl,
                                byte[] postData,
                                java.lang.String postMimeType)
        Submits specified data synchronously to specified URL.

        If destination host is HTTP enabled, use HTTP POST semantics for the submission. Note: Only "application/x-www-form-urlencoded" type data is currently supported as data for submission (any type of data may still be retrieved, though).

        On successful return (UrlResult.getStatus() returns NabtoStatus.OK), UrlResult.getResult() returns the HTML code. The MIME type of the data is returned by UrlResult.getMimeType().

        Parameters:
        nabtoUrl - The URL to submit data to.
        postData - The data to submit.
        postMimeType - MIME type of data to submit.
        Returns:
        A UrlResult object. If the function succeeds, the return value of UrlResult.getStatus() is NabtoStatus.OK. If the function fails, the return value of UrlResult.getStatus() is one of the following values.
        • NabtoStatus.ERROR_READING_CONFIG: The config file wasn't read.
        • NabtoStatus.INVALID_SESSION: Session handle was invalid. See init(String, String)
        • NabtoStatus.FAILED: Unknown error.

      • getSessionToken

        public java.lang.String getSessionToken()
        Reads the session token of the application's session handle. This token is typically supplied in html requests.
        Returns:
        If the function succeeds, the return value is the session token. If the function fails, the return value is an empty string. This can occur if the Nabto client is not initialized (see init(String, String)) or an unspecified error occurred.
